{"replace_all": false, "file_path": "/home/nico/Work/task-w2t70/repo/README.md", "old_string": "Both camelCase (`categoryId`, `minPrice`, `pageSize`, `availableFrom`, `availableStart`, `availableEnd`) and snake_case (`category_id`, `min_price`, `page_size`, `available_from`, `available_start`, `available_end`) param names are accepted.

**Availability filter behavior**: The `available_from` param selects the day of week. When used alone, it matches any service with at least one availability window on that day. When combined with `available_start` and/or `available_end`, the filter further narrows to windows where `start_time <= available_start` AND `end_time >= available_end` — i.e., the service covers the requested time range. The frontend exposes day, start-time, and end-time controls when the availability filter is active. The time inputs appear conditionally after a day is selected.", "new_string": "Both camelCase (`categoryId`, `minPrice`, `pageSize`, `availableFrom`, `availableTo`) and snake_case (`category_id`, `min_price`, `page_size`, `available_from`, `available_to`) param names are accepted.

**Availability filter behavior**: `availableFrom` / `available_from` selects the day of week (0=Sunday through 6=Saturday). When used alone, it matches any service with at least one availability window on that day. When combined with `availableTo` / `available_to` (HH:MM), the filter further narrows to windows where `end_time >= available_to` on the selected day — i.e., the service is available until at least the requested time. The frontend exposes a day-of-week dropdown and a conditional "Available Until" time input. This maps to the `service_availability_windows` schema (day_of_week + start_time + end_time) and is forward-compatible with future date-range or geo-based availability support."}

